    "body": "This reproduces.....\n\n```\nIn [17]: df = DataFrame(np.arange(15).reshape(5,3),columns=[False,True,2])\n\nIn [18]: df\nOut[18]: \n   False  True   2\n0      0     1   2\n1      3     4   5\n2      6     7   8\n3      9    10  11\n4     12    13  14\n\nIn [19]: mapper = { 0 : 'foo', 1 : 'bar', 2 : 'bah' }\n\nIn [20]: df.rename(columns=mapper)\nOut[20]: \n   foo  bar  bah\n0    0    1    2\n1    3    4    5\n2    6    7    8\n3    9   10   11\n4   12   13   14\n```\n\nHere's the problem\n\n```\nIn [21]: True in mapper\nOut[21]: True\n\nIn [22]: False in mapper\nOut[22]: True\n```\n\nThis is trying each element of the columns (in the example) and doing:\n\n```\nif x in mapper:\n     return mapper[x]\nelse:\n     return x\n```\n\nNot sure of an easy way around this, maybe just use the strings `True` and `False` in your columns?\n"
